@page "/help/reporting"
@attribute [Authorize]

<PageTitle>Reports And Forms</PageTitle>

<section class="page-shell">
    <header class="page-header">
        <div>
            <p class="eyebrow">Reports And Forms</p>
            <h1>Keep printed output precise, reviewable, and easy to reproduce.</h1>
        </div>
        <p class="page-intro">
            Reports and labels are a major business surface in this system. That includes financial statements, customer
            statements, vendor checks, paychecks, tax forms, year-end employee forms, mailing labels, shipment forms,
            and the many supporting layouts an accounting and operations suite depends on.
        </p>
    </header>

    <section class="content-grid">
        <article class="panel">
            <h2>Major output families</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>Financial statements such as trial balance, balance sheet, income statement, and account detail.</li>
                <li>Receivables output such as aging, customer statements, and cash-application review.</li>
                <li>Payables output such as aging, checks, remittance detail, and payment registers.</li>
                <li>Payroll output such as paychecks, payroll registers, tax liabilities, and year-end employee forms.</li>
                <li>Tax-facing forms and schedules that depend on current jurisdiction rules.</li>
                <li>Operations documents and labels such as pick tickets, packing slips, shipment labels, and routing forms.</li>
            </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="panel">
            <h2>Before releasing any report or form</h2>
            <ol class="step-list">
                <li>Confirm the company, period, and filters are correct.</li>
                <li>Verify totals against the owning module or ledger control account.</li>
                <li>Check page breaks, long names, decimal precision, and date formatting.</li>
                <li>Preview realistic data, including awkward addresses and long descriptions.</li>
                <li>Archive the authored source and distribute the published output through release packaging, not Git.</li>
            </ol>
        </article>
    </section>

    <section class="content-grid">
        <article class="panel">
            <h2>Labels and stock-sensitive forms</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>Design for the real stock or printer target, not an abstract page size.</li>
                <li>Keep barcodes, postal blocks, and key identifiers out of printer-margin danger zones.</li>
                <li>Test on the real printer path whenever margins, fonts, or stock change.</li>
                <li>Separate mailing labels, internal labels, and operational labels when their rules differ.</li>
            </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="panel">
            <h2>Authoring stance</h2>
            <ul class="feature-list">
                <li>Commit authored report definitions, tests, and source-side assets.</li>
                <li>Keep generated publish copies such as bundled CSS, maps, and <code>web.config</code> out of Git.</li>
                <li>Keep business rules in stable datasets or application code instead of burying them in a layout tool.</li>
                <li>Treat tax forms, paychecks, and year-end forms as controlled output that deserves explicit review.</li>
            </ul>
        </article>
    </section>
</section>
